Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the pasta.

Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm pieces.

Pop the pepper pieces onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, spread out and roast on the top shelf until soft, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Add the @linguine{200} to the pan of boiling water and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes} then drain in a #colander{}.

Pop back in the pan, drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one).

Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped) (or use scissors).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. When hot, add the @chorizo{60} and mushrooms, fry until they both are golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30}, followed by the @chopped tomatoes with basil{1%finely chopped}, @vegetable stock powder{1}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25} and @water{50}(for the sauce).

Add a pinch of @sugar{pinch} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thick and tomatoey, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When they are ready, combine the roasted pepper, cooked pasta and sauce in whichever pan is the largest.

Stir in half the chives and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40}.

> TIP: Add a splash more water if it seems a bit dry!

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Serve in #bowls{}. Finish with the @walnuts{20} and a sprinkling of the remaining chives and cheese. Enjoy!

== Step 4 MOD ==

> If you've added chorizo to your meal, add to the pan before you add the garlic, tomato puree etc. when you add your mushrooms.

> Fry until the chorizo and mushrooms are golden, ~{2-3%minutes}, add the garlic, cook for ~{30%seconds} stirring frequently. Continue with the rest of the step and recipe as instructed.